# Backend Conventions

When working on the backend submodule (`backend/`), follow these conventions.

## 1. Documentation Location

- **All backend-related docs** live in `backend/docs/`, not in the parent repo `docs/`.
- Add new docs under `backend/docs/` and update `backend/docs/README.md` index.

## 2. Documentation Language

- **All docs in English** except the main Chinese README (`backend/README.md`).
- `backend/README.en.md` is the English README.

## 3. Doc Filenames

- Use **kebab-case** for all files under `backend/docs/`:
  - ✅ `assignable-skills-flow.md`, `import-skill-repo.md`, `skills-submodule-guide.md`
  - ❌ `ASSIGNABLE_SKILLS_FLOW.md`, `ImportSkillRepo.md`

## 4. README Updates

- When adding or changing docs, update:
  - `backend/README.md` (Chinese) — 文档 section
  - `backend/README.en.md` — Documentation section
  - `backend/docs/README.md` — Document index table

## 5. Skills Submodule & Assignable Skills

- **Add/modify skill libraries**: See `backend/.cursor/skills/skills-submodule-guide/SKILL.md` or `backend/docs/skills-submodule-guide.md`.
- **Meta architecture**: Main `meta.json` = sources registry only; each source has `{source}/meta.json` with `skills_dir`, categories + skills. No symlinks; runtime resolves to `_submodules/{source}/{skills_dir}/...`.
- **Import script**: From backend root: `./scripts/import_skill_repo.sh <url> [source]`. When backend is a submodule, run from repo root: `./backend/scripts/import_skill_repo.sh`.

## 6. Path Conventions

- In backend docs and Cursor skills, use paths **relative to backend root**:
  - `skills/assignable_skills/`, `scripts/import_skill_repo.sh`, `docs/`
- When backend is used as submodule, parent docs may reference `backend/docs/...`.
